  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0db8\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0da7 \u0daf\u0db9\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dda \u0daf\u0dd3 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "High price in Dambulla for Jaffna's grape harvest",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Dambulla Economic Center Trade Association says that the price of vegetables in the Dambulla Economic Center has gone down in the past few days and has reached a certain level today (20th).",
        "Also, while the quantity of vegetables from the Jaffna Peninsula is increasing these days, the harvest of mangoes grown in Jaffna is currently being received in large quantities in Dambulla, and last year, a kilo of mangoes sold at a price of between 300 and 350 rupees is fetching 900 rupees today.",
        "They point out that in the last few days, Dambulla Economic Center received between 1300 and 1350 rupees per kilo of grapes received from Jaffna and with the increase in the amount of grapes received by the economic center, the price of grapes has dropped to 900 rupees per kilo.",
        "However, traders point out that there is a high demand for grapes from Jaffna because the importation of methi from foreign countries is very minimal.",
        "The shopkeepers of the economic center point out that the grape harvest reaches the Dambulla Economic Center from Jaffna in small packages at around 4 am and traders from almost all parts of the island come to Dambulla to buy it from Jaffna.",
        "In the last few days, the price of vegetables was going down in the Dambulla Economic Center, however, by the morning of the 20th, the representatives of the Economic Center Trade Association indicated that the price of vegetables increased due to the decrease in the receipt of vegetables with the increase in the number of traders coming to buy vegetables at the economic center.",
        "They further point out that usually the price of vegetables is decided on the theory of supply and demand."
      ],
